## VI, 50. Exorcism of vermin infesting grain in the field.

1\. Slay ye the tarda ('borer'), the samanka ('hook'), and the mole, O
Asvins; cut off their heads, and crush their ribs! Shut their mouths,
that they shall not eat the barley; free ye, moreover, the grain from
danger!  
2. Ho tarda ('borer'), ho locust, ho gabhya ('snapper'), upakvasa! As a
Brahman (eats not) an uncompleted sacrifice, do ye, not eating this
barley, without working injury, get out!  
3. O husband of the tardâ (-female), O husband Of the vaghâ (-female),
ye of the sharp teeth, listen to me! The vyadvaras ('rodents') of the
forest, and whatever other vyadvaras (there are), all these we do crush.

